4. Select "Empty Activity" as the template for your project and click "Next."

5. Set the project details, such as project name, package name, and save location.

6. Choose the minimum SDK version for your APK.

7. Click on "Finish" to create the project.

8. Open the AndroidManifest.xml file in the project structure.

9. Add the required permissions to the `<manifest>` element of the AndroidManifest.xml file, specifying the necessary permissions for your app.

10. Build and run the project on an Android device or emulator to test the auto permission functionality.

11. Generate a signed APK using Android Studio's Build → Build Bundle(s) / APK(s) → Build APK(s) option.

12. Locate the generated APK file in the project's output directory.

13. Distribute the APK to your desired audience.

